CRIMEAN-CONGO HEMORRHAGIC FEVER - PAKISTAN (21): (PUNJAB) NEW CASE
******************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sun 18 Sep 2016
Source: The Express Tribune [edited]
http://tribune.com.pk/story/1183514/congo-fever-case-suspected/


A 35-year-old woman was admitted at Nishtar Medical Hospital on Saturday [17 Sep 2016] with symptoms of Congo fever. A hospital spokesman said NB, a resident of Chak Gabol, Rajanpur [district, Punjab province], had been brought to the DHQ Hospital with symptoms of the Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever on Wednesday [14 Sep 2016].

He said she was later referred to Nishtar Hospital. He said 4 of her children had also been admitted with fever. "However, their fever subsided after intervention and their condition stabilised," he said. Nasreen was admitted to Ward 27. He said her blood samples had been sent to Islamabad for tests. "Meanwhile, an isolation section has been set up for her," he said.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The total number of Crimean-Congo hemorrhagic fever (CCHF) cases from Pakistan as of 22 Sep 2016 (personal communication) is 72 and the following is the distribution by province:
Suspected / Confirmed / Deaths
Punjab: 129 / 14 / 9
Sindh: NA / 9 / 7
Khyber Pakhtunkhwa: 71 / 16 / 5
Balochistan: 104 / 33 / 10

There are increasing efforts at federal and provincial levels to prevent disease transmission from animals to humans with efforts by both human and animal sectors. - Mod.UBA

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4508287,941.]
